-- Iran Automobile Production Drops 40% This Year, Shargh Reports
-- B y   Y e g a n e h   S a l e h i
-- 2012-07-04T08:36:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/iran-automobile-production-drops-40-this-year-shargh-reports.html
Iran ’s car production decreased by as
much as 40 percent in the first three months of the current
Iranian year from the year-ago period,  Shargh  reported, citing
Mohammad-Reza Najafi-Manesh, a member of Iran’s  Automotive Part
Makers Association .  The industry is being hurt by the government’s setting of
prices for domestic cars, he added, according to Shargh.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yeganeh Salehi in Dubai at 
 yalehi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
